<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[491,1542,562,1903]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[523,661,602,628]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Etymology.</emphasis>
Tartaro is the name of a legendary man-eater giant living in the Southwestern French Pyrenees, including the Bearn where the fossil has first been described. 
<emphasis box="[1421,1472,642,667]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">cyon</emphasis>
is the Greek for dog.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
